# Functions to omit from coverage tracking.
#
# Read by scripts/gen_cov_fns.pl: any function named here is dropped from the
# generated cov_fns list, so it never appears in cov.txt / cov.rpt / cov.html.
# Use this for functions that are intentionally untracked (e.g. trivial stubs,
# unreachable crash/NMI paths, or anything that only adds noise to the report).
#
# Format: one function name per line.  Blank lines and lines starting with '#'
# are ignored.  Leading/trailing whitespace is trimmed.
#
# The interactive report (install/cov.html) has a per-function "Omit" button
# that accumulates names locally and lets you download an updated copy of this
# file to commit here.
